Hello my friends!! I’ve missed you all so much!! There’s been so many life things happening, and I ended up taking an unplanned break to fully experience them and be in the moment. 
I think I’m finally ready to start easing back into posting on Instagram and YouTube. I’m not sure what that will look like, but I have really missed connecting with all of you. I’m excited to get you caught up. Thanks for still being here ❤️see you soon! 
📸 @soccerdad430 
#vintage #vintagegirlnextdoor #truevintageootd #fallleaves #vintagelifestyle

“There are no days so delightful as a fine October.” -Alexander Smith 
🍁🍁🍁
We spent part of last week in CA celebrating our anniversary and this guys bday. We hit some theme parks and had a blast at Universal Halloween Horror Nights. 
Oh yeah! Meet my boyfriend, Jason 😊 I’m excited to tell you more about him and all the exciting things we’ve been up to this past year. 
(I got this amazing vintage Swirl dress from @thegoldenpeplum )

“Ford Division’s personal luxury car, the Thunderbird, is named for a legendary bird known to the Native Americans as a good luck omen. The mythical bird was supposed to have caused thunder, lightening, and rain. It symbolized, among other things, power, swiftness, and prosperity.”
(from a Ford Motor Company news release 1955)
